Abyssal beasts are a type of demon players can find in the Senntisten Asylum and the Wilderness. They are the second strongest of the Abyssal Slayer creatures. They require a Slayer level of 105 in order to be harmed.

They are killed for their Jaws of the Abyss drop, a piece of tier 85 melee headgear that benefits players when their enemies are affected by bleeds.

When killed on a Slayer task each kill reduces the count by 2.

Alongside possessing the ability to teleport around like abyssal demons, the abyssal beast will periodically lash its tongue out (far longer and wider than their auto-attack) in a targeted area; if the player does not move from it, they will take moderate melee damage and the beast will heal for the damage the attack would have dealt.

Luck-enhancing items are not required to access the table, but do increase the chance of doing so, as does doing higher-level content.

Update history[edit | edit source]

This information has been compiled as part of the update history project. Some updates may not be included – see here for how to help out!
  • patch 15 January 2024 (Update):
    • Fixed an issue that stopped abyssal lords, abyssal savages, and abyssal beasts from dropping items from the Wilderness shared drop table.
  • patch 10 July 2023 (Update):
    • Abyssal beasts are now less likely to move the player when in combat.
  • patch 7 March 2022 (Update):
    • The spring cleaner will now correctly disassemble or high alchemy orikalkum salvage drops from Abyssal Slayer creatures.
  • update 28 February 2022 (Update):
    • Added to game.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • The abyssal savage, abyssal beast, and abyssal lord were designed by Mod Shogun during Game Jam 2017 and 2018. They were called abyssal hounds during development as shown with the concept art.
  • While attack damage from abyssal beasts are not reduced by protect/deflect prayers, they are reduced by the staff of light special attack.
